info.objectType: Bronze Mould, Valve 2 - for socketed axes
info.description: Matrix/castings: double m-m evident at side of cg.; dec'n uncertain; sl. spatulate shape to lower bl.; near perp. ledge at bottom would give flat-ended bl. e.; inside face, or socket, of cg. with almost half-elliptic cross sec.; walls seem steep and near straight; top of Pb. cg. seems to approximate tt matrix end[;]Mould: tendency to concave outsloped edges to notches in corners of gate support, creating sharp inside angle; top of tongue convex on outer side, more angular on inner; widely spaced but sym. core prints -  vert. elliptical with domed profiles; narrow contact face mainly flat, little part concave below loop - perhaps leaving small cavity here when mould closed; location-tongue prob. orig. continuous variable ^ to rounded sec. - variable height, disappearing close to end of side walls; outer lip where intact has marked concave sec. with thin almost pointed outer fg. angled upwards

info.objectType: Bronze Mould ~ for Socketed Axes; Valve 1
info.description:
Circumstances: found 6 Sept. 1965 on a building site on the north side of Castle Road, during digging of drains for the second house east of the junction between Castle Road and Harefield Avenue; the two halves were found between three & 4 feet apart, at a depth of 18 inches; a subsequent examination yielded no traces of occupation (a).
Dimensions: L (in plane of contact face) 105 mm; max. EW.  46.5; max. B. 24; Matrix: L 75.5; Wbl.e.  29; Wm. 32.4; D upper m-m 15.5; min D lp.  1.8;  D bev. across bl.  6.5; H core prints 2.8 & 3.0.
Casting typology: dable m.m, good bulbous upper one; lp. springs from sl. Lower one & 2 ribs descend – one near straight at first, but both bowed inward; sl. channels franking insides, and one outside of rib; rounded prom., vert., left between ribs; rounded transverse bev. on matrix below rib ends - would create crease; wall sides near straight in sec., body angles fairly crisp; channel - rounded V sec.; approx. ‘V’ groves for ribs.
Mould: near right-angle notches in corners of gate support with concave edges and tendency for acute ridge on inside little in bent; 2 sym. - placed core prints, circ. and domed; contact face variable flat to round sec., but narrows; grove outside also variable in W. and D., mainly V sec.; outer lip, where intact, with rounded crest or ext. facing bev. - joins contact face at top where intervening grove disappears - but is generally lower plane than cont. face; gate support tongue with convex top and rounded angles in long sec.

info.description:
Dimensions: “long d. 88 mm; short d. 73.5; B. Lp.  66.5; B. band 9.3-11.5; ET. terminals approx. 1.0-2.2; T. band max.  (close to Lp. convergence) 11.0; EB. terminals 10.2 (both) ” 

Typology: rod of variable loz. sec., largely sym. except for stretch close to terminals; some tendency to broaden + thicken in inverse relationship, not so marked as on L.44/1; rod flattened at terminals by long tri. facets from face angles forming thin hex. sec.; near intact terminal prob. with semi-circ. end; this curved closer to loop than other

Manufacture: numerous hmks. on bar faces sometimes creating concave or convex sur.; also on angles, forming facets on outside angles at loop convergence, and rippling mainly on internal angles - perhaps decorative; some parts + rod with diag. + longit. scmks – no evid. that recent

Condition: one terminal with corner chipped off – poss. corr. dam. - rest prob. only with p. chipped off; other terminal apparently more dam. - irreg. with dull to light green, and black, sur.

Attached Material: light brown soil traces

Labels/Markings: black ink: 57/346

info.description:
Dimensions: min. E. intact d. 210; max. E. d.  230; T cone 0.4-0.7mm; T. flange 0.5-0.9; E H boss 100

Typology: present tendency to ell [?]  shape not nec. orig.; boss faces, where not crumpled, gently concave; small out turn at crest, consistent on all projections, suggests bead-molding - one even has convex profile surviving; rib molding emphasizing top of step and rim of fg.; latter with semi-circ. section orig.;  Base of step prob. orig. an obtuse angle - fairly crisp, but not extremely; outer fg.  May have been sl.  Sloped orig.
 
Manufacture: tendency to sl. thinner sheet for cone than for surround.
Condition: almost half of outer fg. lost; most of cone crest also broken away, as well as portion of the adjacent cone; one half of piece contorted by number of bends - some quite angular - all assoc. with a dull gold brown colour, and prob. recent dam.; numerous other cracks/fractures, esp. along orig. creases etc.; most edges of fracture reveal purply brown core to metal; all perfs. appear to be dam.

Attached Material: light brown soil traces embedded in areas - more chalky buff inside

Labels/Markings: black print marking: 3652; stuck on paper label: 15

info.description: Dimensions: of block per illustration; face kept parallel and perpendicular to plane of drawing in each view; faces 1 & 3 approx. parallel in cross section, converging a little in long section; Wt. 2125.7 g[;]Matrix 1: internal L 162mm; ext. L 171.5; int. W 52; ext. W 59.5; max. D matrix (intact matrix sur.) 6.2; max D. end 3.8; most of matrix surface smooth, intact, & very gently concave; side walls mainly near & flat standing at 70*; v. slight furrows down length probably tooling marks; patch of surface chipped away - roughened surface, but similar blue-grey colour to rest of matrix; most of surrounding face generally flat with slight modulations - probably intact; lower left corner reduced by damage; depth at wide end fairly consistent, even to tip.[;]Matrix 2: L 193.5 or 160; max W 49 or ?; max D 3.5; surface of matrix rough pocked, sides ill-defined - one virt. straight, other with central [?sevelling]; broad edge very diffuse - two poss. lines of matrix defined by bevels and pittings (shorter length); narrower end virt. pointed; surrounding face undulates - some almost level with matrix surface; colour similar to black;[;]Matrix 3: int. L 131.5mm; external L 135.5; int. max. W. 54.5; max D side wall (one side) 8.2; max D. other side wall 3.5; max D broad end 5.5; most of matrix smooth and very gently concave, more-or-less flat across broad end, but actual edge angle rises slightly in centre; angle of one side wall very straight - slight ridge inside - other wall very concave line, slightly bowed in section and at angle of c. 70*; top end - no distinct bevel line - but no end of dam.; 2 or 3 small patches chipped to rough texture - sim. blue-grey col. to rest of matrix; much of surrounding face flat with slight undulation -largely undam. prob.; depression reducing lower left side wall poss. dam. - but not fresher sur.; also facet across lower right tip prob. dam. - irregular surface but not fresher.[;]Face 4: comparatively irregular; tendency for three furrows on lower parts.[;]Block: pale bluey/greeny grey surface, patches of rusty brown staining?; odd chips at corners with maroon brown surface - prob. more recent; groove across top end and across right side face of face 3 - both look ancient and probably incidental; bottom end slightly hollowed - not smooth, pocked; top end flat; patch of blackening on angle between faces 2 & 3, some moss adhering plus green staining in parts[;]Medium Grained Sandstone
Good condition

info.composition: Res. Lab XRF determination (on Matrices 1 & 3) did not detect any significant peaks for[;]Cu, Sn, As, Pb; The stone would appear to have significant quantities[;]of Fe, Po, Ca, Ti, Si.
info.description:
Dimensions: of blook (sic) as per illustration: face kept parallel and perpendicular[;]to plane of drawing in each view; faces 1 & 3 approx. parallel in cross-section, converging a[;]little in long-section; [;]
Matrix 1: internal L: 162; ext. L: 171.5; int. W: 52; ext. W: 59.5; Max D:[;]matrix (intact matrix sur.) 6.2; max. D. end 3.8; most of matrix sur. smooth, intact, & v. gently[;]concave; side walls mainly neat & flat, standing at ~70°; v. slight furrows down length[;]prob. tooling marks; patch of sur. chipped away - roughened sur., but sim. blue-grey colour to  rest of[;]matrix; most of surrounding face generally flat with sl. indentations - prob. intact; lower left corner[;]reduced by damage; depth at wide end fairly consistent, even to tip;[;]
Matrix 2: L: 193.5 or 160; max. W 48 or ?; max. D. 3.5; surface of matrix[;]rough pocked; sides ill-defined - one virt. straight, other with central swelling; broad edge v. diffuse -[;]two poss. lines of matrix defined by bevels and pittings (shorter length); narrower end virt. pointed;[;]surrounding face undulates - some almost level with matrix sur.;  colour sim. to block;[;]
Matrix 3: int. L: 131.5; external L: 135; int. max. W 54.5; max. D. side weld (one[;]side) 8.2; max. D. other side weld 3.5; max D broad end: 5.5; most of matrix smooth and v.[;]gently concave, more-or-less flat across broad end, but actual edge angle rises slightly[;]in centre; angle of one side wall v. straight - slight ridge inside - other wall v. concave line slightly bowed[;]in section and at angle of c. 70°; top end - no distinct bevel line - but no end of[;]dam.; 2 or 3  small patches chipped to rough texture - sim. blue-grey col. to rest of matrix; P.T.O.[;]much of surrounding face flat with slight undulation - largely undam. prob.; depression reducing lower left side wall poss. dam. - but[;]not fresher sur.; also facet across lower right tip prob. dam. - irreg. sur. but not fresher;[;]
Face 4: comparatively irregular; tendency for three furrows on lower parts.[;]
Block: pale bluey/greeny grey sur., patches of rusty brown staining?; odd chips at corners with marroon-brown sur. - prob. more recent; groove across[;]top end and across right side face of face 3 - both look anc. and prob. incidental; bottom end slightly hollowed - not smooth, pocked; top end flat;[;]patch of blackening on angle between faces 2 & 3, some moss adhering plus green staining in parts.[;]
Medium grained sandstone.

info.description:
DIMENSIONS:  L  74.2  mm;  W 25.5;  B end 12.0;  
B loop 7.1;  Wt. 21.7 g. 

TYPOLOGY:  beading at either mouth variable rounded to flattened; beading round side opening flattened where broadens at either end; 2 bevelled surfaces on inside of loop - on one side much more steeply angled than other; line of og.[??} flash visible inside loop - still a ridge towards ends, but seems worn in centre (perhaps by strap?)

CONDITION:  breaks at side and at mouth, both ancient - metal at latter very firm

ATTACHED MATERIALS:  pale fawn soil and chalky deposits embedded in corrosion.

info.surface: Speckled black/grey stone with pink tinges; face around Matrix 2 much blackened - esp. up to 5mm from edge of matrix; odd two patches of darkening only around matrix 1; ends and sides also with some darkening. Crack in stone across one side; occasional chip out of edge, especially at top of mould beside respective mouth-mouldings; inside of two matrix 1 loops very battered - that of Matrix 2 only a little; ribs, scorings of M.2 still quite crisp; ribs seem worn on M.1; flaw in stone on lower blade of matrix 2.
info.collection: Salisbury, Sals, & S. Wilts. Museum[;]Formerly in Pitt Rivers Museum, Farnham, Dorset, P 1173[;]Purchased as Lot 120 at Sotheby's Sale of Duke Collection, July 1895
info.description: Dimensions: Length: Matrix 1: 13.7mm; Matrix 2: 107mm[;]Width: blade Matrix 1: 47mm; blade Matrix 2 41mm; Width mouth Matrix 1: 47mm; Width mouth Matrix 2: 52mm; Width axe face beneath moulding Matrix 1: 32.5mm; Width axe face beneath moulding Matrix 2: 34mm; Width body below loop Matrix 1: 38.5mm; Width body below loop Matrix 2: 42.5mm[;]Depth moulding Matrix 1: 9.5mm; Depth moulding Matrix 2: 8.5mm[;]Length ribs Matrix 1: 59mm (below base of moulding); Length ribs Matrix 2 53mm (below base of moulding)[;]Depth matrix at moulding Matrix 1: 22mm; Depth matrix at moulding Matrix 2: 20.5mm[;]Wedge-shaped block, opposite faces converging; ends flat and also not quite parallel; sides bowed, thin end: two grooves off long edge with smaller notch in between, v. slight groove off either side?; thick end: central groove, other diffuse notches flanking - poss. damage; Matrix 1: marked ledge below slightly splayed moulding; rectangular body section with rib-emphasised corners; 3 straight slightly converging ribs; two loops - one springing from moulding, other from just below; spatulate blade forms towards edge; loop grooves with neat 'V' section; one corner rib continues straight where body expands; ribs 'V' sectioned. Matrix 2: upside down from Matrix 1; ledge under slightly splayed moulding; bowed rectangular body section - sides more splayed; rib-emphasised, or crisp body corners; three parallel ribs, not evenly spaced; loop groove with near 'V' section, springing from just below moulding; body parallel sided for much of axe; ribs 'V' sectioned, and tail away to nothing.

info.objectType: Stone Mould (Socketed Axes ) 2 matrices[;]thin sectioned ~ B.M. (Nat. Hist.)
info.description: White Ink Inscr.: "Mould in syenite. Lot 120, Soth. July 95, Duke Coll: found near Bulford, Amesbury. P: 1173."[;]Wedge-shaped block, opposite faces converging; ends flat and also not quite parallel; sides bowed; thin end: two grooves off long edge with smaller notch in between, v. slight groove off either side ?; thick end: central groove, other diffuse notches flanking - poss. damage[;] Matrix 1: marked ledge below slightly splayed moulding; rectangular body section with rib - emphasised corners; 3 straight slightly converging ribs; two loops - one springing from moulding, other just below; spatulate blade forms towards edge; loop grooves with near "V" section; one corner rib continues straight where body expands; ribs "V" sectioned[;]Matrix 2: upside down from Matrix 1; ledge under slightly splayed moulding; bowed rectangular body section - sides more splayed; rib-emphasised, or crisp body corners; three parallel ribs, not evenly spaced; loop groove with near "V" section, springing from just below moulding; body parallel sided for much of axe; ribs "V" sectioned and tail away to nothing
info.associations: Speckled black/grey stone with pink tinges; face around Matrix 2 much blackened - esp. up to 5mm from edge of matrix; odd two patches of darkening only around Matrix 1; ends and sides also with some darkening; Crack in stone across one side; occasional chip out of edge, especially at top of mould beside respective mouth mouldings; inside of two matrix 1 loops very battered - that of Matrix 2 only a little; ribs, sconing of M. 2 still quite crisp; ribs seem worn on M.1; flaw in stone on lower blade of matrix 2.

info.composition: Metallurgy - Analyst: BM Res. Lab - Craddock; Bibliog: File 4532; Composition: CU 66.5; Pb 21.6; Sn 8.2; AS 1.5; Sb 0.23; Bi 0.8; Ni 0.24; Ag 0.06; Co 0.014; Zn 0.02; Fe 0.03
info.description: Dimensions: max dimension 69.0mm; EL tube possibly full L 43.5; B tube (middle) 24.7; Wt. 186.8g[;]Typology: craggy lump of bronze incorporating half-melted implements: (1) tube with flanged opening on one side at presumed centre, and tube here a little swollen with rounded ridge encircling and continuing onto flange to give very slightly lentrical shape to opening; edge of flange not a regular shape in profile and pres. broken, but surface more smooth; more intact end of tube with slight expansion to ridge and outer bevelled perimeter; basically amorphous lump protruding from this end, may be part of an original rod-like extension; side opening is blocked just below level of tube surface-apparently continuous casting, no crack apparent. (2) short stretch of curved rod of eye-shaped section; length of 13mm of concave face exposed before swallowed by lump; outer face concealed; outer end very rounded - looks most like runner of casting jet, more elliptical than known fleshhook prongs. (3) 'strip' in edge of lump EL 15mm, T 1.5-2.5 - apparently a little twisted along length W of end exposed on face (1) 7.3. (4) 'strip' - with 3 apparent mouldings on exposed face - parallel; EL 10.8; W 9.5 (5) A few other small projections - more amorphous and uncertain whether parts of object.

info.description: Dimensions: max. dimension 69.0; EL tube (possibly full L) 43.5; B tube (middle) 24.7 [;] Typology: craggy lump of bronze incorporating half-melted implements: (1) tube with flanged opening on one side at presumed centre, and tube here a little swollen with rounded ridge encircling and continuing onto flange to give v. slightly lentoid shape to opening; edge of flange not a regular shape in profile and pres. broken, but surface now smooth; more intact end of tube with slight expansion to ridge and outer bevelled perimeter; basically amorphous lump protruding from this end, may be part of an original rod-like extension; side opening is blocked just below level of tube surface - apparently continuous casting, no crack apparent. [;] (2) short stretch of curved rod of eye-shaped section; length of 13mm of concave face exposed before swallowed by lump; outer face concealed; outer end v. rounded. - looks most like runner of casting jet , more elliptical than known flesh hook prongs. [;] (3) 'strip' in edge of lump EL 15mm, T 1.5-2.5 - apparently a little twisted along length W of end exposed on face (1) 7.3 [;] (4) 'strip' - with 3 apparent mouldings on exposed face - parallel; EL 10.8; W 9.5 [;] (5) a few other small  projections - more amorphous and uncertain whether parts of objects. [;] Metallurgy-Analyst: BM Res. Lab. - Craddock [;] Bibliog. File 4532 [;] Composition: Cu 66.5, Pb 21.6, Sn 8.2, As 1.5, Sb 0.23, Bi 0.8, Ni 0.24, Ag 0.06, Co 0.014, Zn 0.02, Fe 0.03 (continued)
